<Author>jeep_potter
<Content>Good low cost accomadation in Berlin 9 of us stopped here in October 2008. I had booked 3 triple rooms via the hotel website. On arrival we were placed in 3 rooms with 6 beds in each! The cost per person for 3 nights was 96 Euros which included breakfast.Breakfast is served from 7am until noon in the bar/reception area on the 4th floor. It consisited of a wide selection of cereals, fruit, cheeses, cooked meats and bread. Coffee and Tea were available. Orange Juice was 1.5 Euros at the bar.The rooms were very large. There was no TVs in the rooms. The bathrooms were basic but clean, The showers were especially powerful. My room over looked the courtyard.The hotel had a bar at reception which stayed open until about 3am. Smoking is allowed in the bar which pleased and displeased some of our group.The Transit is situated just off a main street. It's handy for the nightlife in Bergmanstrasse, and if you want to travel further afield then the U-Bahn station (Mehringdham) is about a 6-8 minute walk.Overall I thought the hotel was value for money. The rooms were clean, the staff were courteous and helpful, and the location was good. 
