<Author>JohnBlack
<Content>Best showers in all Europe I love this hotel! It is a renovated cigar factory - so the ceilings are very high and the windows are huge. All the rooms open onto the central courtyard and are flooded with sunlight. So is the large common room, making breakfast a delight. The rooms are done all in white and grey - comfortable, spotlessly clean, and tastefully spare. I took the bargain rate, as I have no qualms about a bath down the hall. The bathroms are large, there is never a wait, and the Transit has the best showers in all Europe - a torrent of hot water.The checkin desk doubles as a bar - open all day and half the night, always tended by friendly people.Best part: you are in an interesting, vibrant, nieghborhood, not on the tourist route. A short walk to the nearest U-Bahn puts you anywhere in the city within a few minutes. John BlackWashington, DC 
